name: Black Label Retreats
description: Welcome to BLR Gisborne! Nestled in the stunning hinterland of Gisborne, New Zealand, our retreat is all about indulgence and relaxation. From our hilltop geodesic dome, you‚Äôll catch the sunrise before anyone else and enjoy amazing views of the ocean, rolling hills, and vineyards.
neighborhood_overview:
Gisborne, a charming city nestled on the eastern shores of New Zealand's North Island, holds the distinction of being the first to witness the sunrise in the world. Offering a delightful climate and an array of captivating attractions, Gisborne warmly welcomes visitors to explore its many wonders.

Affectionately known as "Gizzy," this vibrant city boasts an array of treasures that cater to every taste and interest. From its pristine beaches that beckon with their golden sands and azure waters to its intriguing historical sites that whisper tales of the past, Gisborne offers a rich tapestry of experiences.

The city's vibrant culture shines through its diverse offerings, including numerous wineries that invite you to embark on delightful vineyard tours and savor the flavors of locally crafted wines. Outdoor enthusiasts will find themselves in paradise, with an abundance of hiking trails that lead to breathtaking vistas of the sea and the surrounding landscapes.
host_about: Hamish Armstrong is a laid-back, attentive host who knows how to connect with everyone. He‚Äôs all about making sure his guests have a great time, taking pride in delivering top-notch service and ensuring every stay is enjoyable.

name: Mahaanui Cottage Farmstay Experience, Gisborne NZ
description:
Mahaanui Cottage is a fully furnished, self-contained, private, country cottage located in the beautiful Tiniroto, halfway between Gisborne (~2.5 hr drive) and Wairoa (~1.5 hr drive). With everything you need for an enjoyable stay, it's perfect for friends and families looking for a relaxing country break. Or an active farm experience.

Drive from Auckland Airport - 8 hrs.
Drive from Napier Airport - 3 hrs.
Drive from Gisborne Airport - 2.5 hrs.

Note: Drive times are longer due to Cyclone G.
neighborhood_overview:
Doneraille Park is 2 minutes drive away. The park is a popular picnic, camping and swimming spot on our Hangaroa River.

The secret waterfall is 10 minutes drive down the road. It is a lovely picnic spot that locals enjoy. In the Summer, you can slide off the waterfall, jump in from the rocks and from behind the falls themselves.

There is private farm access for trout fishing, swimming or kayaking.

Some other nearby landmarks to check out include the Hackfalls Arboretum, Eastwood Hill Arboretum, Rere Rockslide and Te Reinga Falls / Ruakituri Valley ‚Äì well known for its excellent trout fishing (Currently No Access - Te Reinga Bridge Destroyed in Cyclone Gabrielle).
host_about: Simon and I own Mahaanui, a 615 hectare hill country sheep and beef farm in Tiniroto, near Gisborne. We also host guests from NZ and around the world in our Mahaanui cottage and Mahaanui Quarters. We love including them in our farm activities and teaching visitors about farm practices, stock and land management as well as introducing them to our work dogs and pet animals.

name: A Cabin in the Country
description:

name: Lake Waikaremoana - Tuai Cottage
description: Welcome to Tuai Cottage.  Our home is one of the original Public Works houses in Tuai that provided accommodation to staff working at the Power Station.  Although it has been modernised a bit, we have tried to retain the original feel of the house.   Although part of the village, you can sit on the deck, look out over our garden and feel you are well located on the edge of the forest.
neighborhood_overview: Originally built last century for the dairyman to serve the power station community, this house became our holiday home and currently our primary home about 10 years ago.  We are located ten minutes drive from one end of the Lake Waikaremoana Great Walk.  High on a hill, the house overlooks the village of Tuai and Lake Whakamarino.  Sitting on the deck, you can imagine that you are in the middle of the bush as there are no houses visible - peace and relaxation abound.
host_about: Leon and I are semi-retired people who - unexpectedly - find ourselves living up near Lake Waikaremoana, a place of great contentment and great fishing.  Our working lives have revolved around the care of children and young people and this environment allows Leon plenty of time for writing.  We have lived in USA, Europe, the Middle East and - best of all - New Zealand.  We continue to enjoy travelling, particularly to visit our grandchildren in Colorado.  Although our house is compact, guests can be as social or as private as they wish.

name: Tokomaru Beach
description: Our place is newly built, behind a historic building, only metres from the beautiful Tokomaru Bay Beach. The facilities are all modern, with heat pump/air conditioning, acomodating 4 people  with style, comfort and ease. One queen bed is in the lounge as a pull down/retractable and the second in a separate bedroom. Shower and toilet is an ensuite shared by all guests but accessed through the bedroom.
neighborhood_overview:
Our place at Tokomaru Beach is only metres from this pristine East Coast Beach, and a short walk from a fully stocked if small, supermarket, gas station, excellent fish and chips, along with a stunning new cafe.
There is also the local Tavern, a 'Must Visit' for relaxed dinners, coffee on the deck overlooking the bay, and more.
All of these amenities are easily reached by a stunning stroll along the beach, or making use of the brand new paved footpaths around town, or the wide grass walk ways.
Tokomaru Beach itself is one of New Zealands great coastal ( secret) treasures - 5km or so of white sand walking, listening to the surf, excellent swimming in the waves and/or the beach lagoons for little ones, fishing and surfing ( reef) for those looking for more.
host_about:
Hi  we are Barry & Pam - happy, married and we love the beach, run a small art gallery and enjoy sharing this special part of New Zealand with visitors. Pam is a midwife/nurse and Barry an engineer with the local council. We enjoy a pristine environment, a wonderful beach where you can swim in the waves, fish, ride a horse or just stroll and leave all your cares behind. We have three adult children and 7 grand children.

Tokomaru Bay is one hour north of Gisborne. A smallish community of about 500 and boasts a great beach, old ruins to explore, very good 4 Square supermarket, cafe, pub & restaurant and plenty of coastline to enjoy. We first visited Toko 44 years ago and now we live here -  nothing seems to change, we kind of like that!
Just in front of our BnB is an old 1926 billiard hall we are renovating to be our home -  in the mean time we have an art gallery and studio in the front.

The BnB is just over the road from the beach -  you walk out of the front door past the billiard hall and straight over a quiet road onto the beach. Love it so much we thought perhaps you might also.
